               <p>EVAN EVANS. I am a <rs id="t18180506-40-viclabel225" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-40-victim401 t18180506-40-viclabel225"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18180506-40-crimeloc226">Bishopsgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180506-40-crimeloc226" type="placeName" value="Bishopsgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180506-40-crimeloc226" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-40-off223 t18180506-40-crimeloc226"></join>. On the 25th of April, about half-past eleven o'clock at night, as I was shutting up, I saw the prisoner go into the shop - I got in as soon as I could; he asked me if I had any second-hand braces to sell? I told him I had some new ones at 18d. a pair - He said they were too dear. He was going out, I suspected him, and asked him what was under his apron? laid hold of him, and found eight yards of kerseymere between his legs. I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
